Generally, they try to let everyone in for 61C when the semester starts, much like 61AB. People on the waitlist are usually undeclared majors, like me. But because of the situation of COVID-19 and TA staffing issues, I'm not confident it'll be the same.

I'll let an instructor or TA give input.

history.content:
You can expect to see some increases to enrollment soon after the University announces its plan for F20.

I cannot say how much the class will expand at this point, but I've been holding enrollment for Fall low until we know if/how to deal with physical distancing requirements in the lab/discussion sections. Please keep in mind that even if the decision is made to teach remotely only, that we do still have budget and hiring constraints that may limit how many online sections we can offer.

Thanks for your patience while things are worked out behind the scenes.
There are only roughly 80 empty seats for 61C, but 400 people are still on the waitlist. I wonder whether there will be more open seats.
